                <h1>Exploring the Rich History of West Virginia</h1>
                <p>West Virginia's history is rich and complex, shaped by its indigenous peoples, colonial influences, and the Civil War. Established in 1863, it became a key player in the industrial revolution with coal mining. The state's struggles and triumphs reflect the resilience of its people, making West Virginia a unique chapter in American history.</p>
